# Ghost System Governance: CSS & Styling Rules

## 1. Styling Strategy & SSOT
- **Single Source of Truth:** `src/app/globals.css` is the ONLY global stylesheet allowed.
- **Forbidden:** Creating new global CSS files in `src/styles/` is strictly prohibited.
- **Tailwind-First:** All styling must be done via Tailwind utility classes.
  - ✅ `bg-background text-text p-4`
  - ❌ `background-color: #040013; color: #fff; padding: 1rem;`
- **Exceptions:** Complex animations or vendor library overrides may use CSS Modules or `globals.css` but must be documented.

## 2. Design Tokens & Variables
- **Colors:** Use semantic names, NOT hex codes.
  - ✅ `text-primary`, `bg-surface`
  - ❌ `text-[#0048ff]`, `bg-[#0b0d3a]`
- **Typography:** Use the fluid type scale variables.
  - ✅ `text-h1`, `text-body`
  - ❌ `text-[32px]`

## 3. Z-Index Scale (Strict Layering)
- `z-0`: Default content
- `z-10`: Elevated components (Cards, Dropdowns)
- `z-40`: Sticky Navbars
- `z-50`: Modals & Overlays
- `z-100`: Critical System Alerts/Toasts
- **Rule:** Do not use arbitrary z-indexes (e.g., `z-[9999]`). Stick to the scale.

## 4. Component Structure
- **Root Element:** All major sections must be wrapped in `.std-grid` to ensure alignment.
- **Responsive:** Mobile-first approach. Write for generic mobile first, then `md:`, `lg:`.
  - ✅ `flex flex-col md:flex-row`
  - ❌ `flex-row max-md:flex-col`

## 5. Maintenance
- **Linting:** Pay attention to CSS specificity. Avoid `!important` unless overriding an external library that uses inline styles.
- **Clean Up:** Delete unused classes. Do not leave commented-out styles.
